It looks like winter will be good for German tourism business:
According to one study, the number of travel bookings for the coming months increased significantly from the previous year - by over 30 percent during the winter season.
Despite weak economic growth, the desire of Germans to travel remains unshaken.
Travel agencies saw a 31 percent increase in winter season bookings compared with the same period last year, the German Travel Association (DRV) reported in Berlin on Monday.
