The company's management blames the fall in Fortis stock on uncertainty in the overseas market related to the adoption of the US $700 billion package.
The stock was up a little on Monday.
On Friday, the new CEO, Filip Dierckx, was appointed as the bank's new head.
The FMI has also been looking for private buyers, but no one has come forward with a more serious offer.
The Belgian Government has previously stated that investors do not have to worry about losing their money.
The bank's customers have not yet panicked and the bank's branches have not been attacked.
